A painter is on top of a ladder when the ladder tips back and starts to fall over. \\

\noindent Which action is \textbf{less} harmful to the painter?
\begin{enumerate}
	\item[A)] Let go of the ladder at the top.
	\item[B)] Hold on to the ladder all the way to the ground.
\end{enumerate}

\noindent Can you support or prove your answer?
